      <body>

         <div type="slide">
            <head>What is GitHub?</head>
            <figure>
               <graphic width="700px" url="media/GitHub-Logo.png"></graphic>
            </figure>
            <p>GitHub is a code hosting platform for version control and collaboration. It lets you and others work together on projects from anywhere.</p>
         </div>


         <div type="slide">
            <div>
            <head>Step 1: Create a GitHub account</head>
            <list>
               <item><ref target="https://github.com/">https://github.com/</ref></item>
            </list>
            </div>
            <div>
               <head>Step 2: Install GitHub</head>
               <list>
                  <item><ref target="https://github.com/">https://git-scm.com/downloads</ref></item>
                  <item>2a. Commandline</item>
                  <item>2b. GUI Client, e.g. GitHub Desktop <ref target="https://github.com/">https://desktop.github.com/</ref></item>
               </list>
            </div>            
         </div>
         
         
         <div type="slide">
            
            <head>Step 2a: Use GitHub on the Commandline</head>
           
           <list>
              <item>Configure your username and email
              <list>
                 <item><code>git config --global user.name "Martina Scholger"</code></item>
                 <item><code>git config --global user.name "Martina Scholger"</code></item>
              </list>
              </item>
              <item>Open datathon repository on GitHub and clone it
               <list>
                  <item><ref target="https://github.com/distantreading/2021-09-datathon">https://github.com/distantreading/2021-09-datathon</ref></item>
                  <item><code>git clone https://github.com/distantreading/2021-09-datathon.git</code></item>
               </list>
                 <figure>
                    <graphic url="media/github-datathon.png"></graphic>
                 </figure>
              
              </item>
              
           </list>
           
        
         </div>
         
         <div type="slide">
            
            <head>Step 2a: Use GitHub on the Commandline</head>
            
            <list>
               <item>
                  Add your file to the repository
                  <list>
                     <item>
                        Update the local version of a repository from a remote repository<lb /> 
                        <code>git pull origin main</code>
                     </item>
                     <item>
                        Checking the status of the repository<lb />
                        <code>git status</code>
                     </item>
                     <item>
                        Save your file to the folder <code>Work/Texts/</code>
                     </item>
                     <item>
                        Add your file to the git staging area<lb /> 
                        <code>git add mytext.xml</code>
                     </item>
                     <item>
                        Provide a commit message<lb />
                        <code>git commit -m "My first commit"</code>
                     </item>
                     <item>
                        Pushing commits to a remote repository<lb />
                        <code>git push origin main</code>
                     </item>
                  </list>
               </item>
            </list>
         </div>
         
         <div type="slide">
            
            <head>Step 2b: GUI Client fo GitHub</head>
            
            
            <list style="clear:both">
               <item>
                  Install <title>GitHub Desktop</title>
               </item>
               <item>
                  <code>File > Clone respository</code>
                  <figure>
                     <graphic url="media/clone.png"></graphic>
                  </figure>
               </item>
               <item>
                  Save your file to the folder <code>Work/Texts/</code>
               </item>
               <item>
                  Make sure your local repository is up to date<lb />
                  <code>Fetch origin</code>
               </item>
               <item>
                  Provide a summary and "Commit to main"
               </item>
               <item>
                  Push local changes to remote
               </item>
               
               
               
               
           
            </list>
            <figure>
               <graphic url="media/github-desktop.png"></graphic>
            </figure>
         </div>
         
         <div type="slide">
            <head>ELTeC on GitHub</head>
            <list>
               <item><ref target="https://github.com/COST-ELTeC">https://github.com/COST-ELTeC</ref></item>
               <item>Choose your language collection</item>
               <item>Clone repository</item>
            </list>
            
            <figure>
               <graphic url="media/eltec-github.png" width="50%"></graphic>
            </figure>
         </div>
         

         <div type="slide">
            <head>GitHub documentation</head>
            <p><ref target="http://git-scm.com/documentation">http://git-scm.com/documentation</ref></p>
         </div>

         

